Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Getty Museum
Description: A beautifully constructed art museum in the Pacific Palisades, containing works from Ancient Greece, Rome, Etruria as well as some contemporary pieces

Name: LA County Museum of Arts
Description: The largest art museum on the west coast of the US, holding many modern and contemporary artworks, as well as Latin and American art, Asian, Greek, Roman, Etruscan and Islamic artworks. Famous for its iconic set of street lights at its entrance and proximity to the La Brea Tar Pits.

Name: Philadelphia Museum of Art
Description: A Philadelphia art museum that holds many historical paintings, textiles, and other artifacts along with modern and contemporary pieces. Famous in pop culture for its long set of stairs seen in the film ""Rocky"

Name: American Museum of Natural History
Description: A natural history museum on the Upper West side of Manhattan that has collections of over 34 million specimens of plants, animals, fossils, rocks, human remains, and cultural artifacts

Name: The Metropolitan Museum of Art
Description: The largest art museum in the US, located in the Upper East Side of Manhattan. Contains classical works, ancient Egyptian, sculptures from most of the European masters, weapons, and armor from around the world.
